<setup>

  <selectFromSequence name="a" from="-4" to="-1" step="1" />
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="1" to="3" step="1"/> 

  <function name="fLeft" domain="[-5,$b - 0.1)">(x-$a)</function>
  <!-- <label positionFromAnchor="right"><m>f</m></label> -->
  <function name="fRight" domain="($b + 0.1, 5]">(x-$a)</function>  
  <endpoint name="hole" open="true" draggable="false">($b, $b-$a)</endpoint>
  <point name="labelAnchor">($b+1, $b-$a-1)</point>

  <function name="line"> x-$a </function>
  
</setup>

<p>

Consider the function <m>f(x) = \frac{<math simplify>x^2 - ($a+$b)x + $a*$b</math>}{<math simplify>x-$b</math>}</m>
</p>

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        Observe that the domain of <m>f</m> includes all real numbers with a single exception.  What real number is not in the domain of <m>f</m>? 
      </p>  
      <p>
        The domain of <m>f</m> is all real numbers except <answer><award>$b</award></answer>.
      </p>  
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        The quadratic expression, <m><math simplify>x^2 - ($a+$b)x + $a*$b</math></m> in the numerator of <m>f</m> can be factored. 
      </p>
      <p>
        Doing so, we find that <m><math simplify>x^2 - ($a+$b)x + $a*$b</math> = </m><answer><award>(x-$a)(x-$b)</award></answer>.
      </p>  
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        Notice that there is a common factor of <m><math simplify>(x-$b)</math></m> in both the numerator and denominator of <m>f</m>, and this means that provided <m>x \ne $b</m>, we have <m>\frac{x-$b}{x-$b} = 1</m>.
      </p>  
      <p>
        Use this observation to give a simpler formula for <m>f(x)</m> that is valid for all <m>x \ne $b</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
        If <m>x \ne $b</m>, then <m>f(x) = </m><answer>x-$a</answer>.
      </p>  
    </li>
    <li>
      <p> Which of the following graphs correctly represents the given function <m>y = f(x) = \frac{<math simplify>x^2 - ($a+$b)x + $a*$b</math>}{<math simplify>x-$b</math>}</m>?</p>
      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell>

            <graph xmin="-5" xmax="5" ymin="-8" ymax="8" size="small" showNavigation="false">
              $line
              <text name="fxn" anchor="$labelAnchor">  
                <m>y = f(x)</m>
              </text>
              
            </graph>  
                      
          </cell>  
          <cell>

            <graph xmin="-5" xmax="5" ymin="-8" ymax="8" size="small" showNavigation="false">
              $fLeft
              $fRight
              $hole
              <text name="fxn" anchor="$labelAnchor">  
                <m>y = f(x)</m>
              </text>
              
            </graph>  
                      
          </cell>           
          <cell>

            <graph xmin="-5" xmax="5" ymin="-8" ymax="8" size="small" showNavigation="false">
              $fLeft
              $fRight
              $hole
              <text name="fxn" anchor="$labelAnchor">  
                <m>y = f(x)</m>
              </text>
              <point>($b,$b-$a-2)</point>
              
            </graph>  
                      
          </cell>   
        </row>  
        <row>
          <cell halign="center">A</cell>
          <cell halign="center">B</cell>
          <cell halign="center">C</cell>
        </row>  
      </tabular>  
      <p>The correct representation of the graph of <m>f(x)</m> is <answer><award>B</award></answer>.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>  
</p>
  
